26 OCTAVIUS

The Latin os the Octavius reflects the action of these various influences. Within its forty chapters it has been computed that there are two hundred and thirty words in all not found in lexicons of Cicero.¹ Some of these are new words coined by Minucius or introduced by him first into literature. There are many archaisms, Graecisms, poetic expressions and constructions‚ confu- sions of simples and compounds, besides a large number of abstract and derivative terms.
